node.text:
Visit @SculptMovements 💕 for workouts, routine, and everythin else you eed to become fit! .
Treino de MMI com 01. Agachamento máquina 15/12/10 + drop com extensora 4 x 4 / 4x3 / 4x2 /4x 1 aumentando a carga ( 1 série ) 
1 x 10 com pico de contração em cima + 10 saindo da inércia 
1 x 10 com excêntrica lenta + 10 concêntrica lenta + 10 
02. Stiff 3 x 15 + bom dia 10 
03. Flexora 9 x 6 alternando a carga entre leva e pesado 
1 x 30 curtas + 10 isometria + 12 
1 x unilateral 8 /7/6 até zerar sem intervalo 
04. Flexora em pé 3 x 12 parando no meio + glúteo no cabo 3 x 12 
Panturrilhas sempre 😅
Macacão @santtaloren
.
.
.

Lately I have been obsessed with leg day! For the longest time I dreaded leg days because they were 1) so freaking hard & 2) It’s taken a long time to see any progress physically in my legs. I will say I enjoy pushing myself with legs & seeing how strong I am! 

Upper body day will always be my fav, but I no longer hate leg days either 🥰 here’s a preview of what I do on my full lower body days! Most of the time I try to have a designated quad/booty & hamstring/booty day, but today I decided to hit it all! 💪🏼

Credit mindof_kels

Need a new Abs workout? 🔥 Visit @SculptMobility for daily pain management, flexibility, and workout advice📚

tag a friend & visit @EatsConnoisseur for daily delicious foods & recipes to get you slim🥝🍓🍌🍇 

Cheesy Twice Baked Potatoes. Follow the recipe👇🏻
- Pierce a potato with a fork and bake it at 425 degrees F for an hour
- Slice the top off the potato and scoop out the inside
- Combine the scooped potato with 1 tablespoon of sour cream, 1 tablespoon of butter, 1 tablespoon of parmesan cheese, 1 tablespoon of shredded cheddar, 1 teaspoon of smoked paprika, 1 teaspoon of onion powder, and a pinch of salt and pepper
- Transfer the mixture to a ziploc bag or piping bag and add it to the hollowed out potato
- Bake for another 20 minutes at 425 F, garnish with chopped chives

Credit @thejoshelkin

Ladies you NEED to check out @SculptSwim for summers hottest bikinis 👙 

I’m going home tomorrow (haven’t seen my mom in 6 months 😭 😭) and packing 🧳 is never fun 🤯 so at least this workout isn’t too complicated 😬😝😝 simple & effective 👌🏽
👉🏽 Beginners: 2-3 rounds
👉🏽 Advanced: 4-5 rounds
⁉️ Why does this work your core as well as your glutes? Because you should focus on keeping your core engaged in order to keep your hips square (not twisting/dropping) and to prevent your back from arching 🍑 
Credit @zoehappyfit

node.text: Ladies you NEED @SculptSwim for the hottest looks this summer 👙

INTENSE LEGS 🥵🔥
please be sure to LIKE & SAVE the video thank you so so much for the love & support

not even exaggerating a tiny bit when I say that these intense leg workout are pure evil and makes you go 🥲😤💦 but dayyum there’re effective 😌 here’s a lil something to start your week with. I’m here for dizzz LETS GET IT SIS

METHOD: 3-4 rounds x 30 sec rest time as minimal as possible | 2min between rounds

1️⃣ deficit reverse lunge // 20sec each leg
2️⃣ box jumps // 30sec
3️⃣ pistol squat to reverse lunge // 30sec this was a good idea in my head 🥵🤯😂
4️⃣ overhead squat jumps // 30sec
5️⃣ narrow pulse lunges // 30sec

song is but a dream by g-eazy

Credit @hannaoeberg #Fitness #fitfam #fitspo #motivation #workout #workoutvideo #legday #gym #abs
